div#billing-info-step
  // ─── Shared guide wrapper ───
  div.buckets-guide-container
    // ───────── Title & intro ─────────
    h2 💳 Get Your Billing Spreadsheet Ready
    p
      | Before importing your <strong>Billing</strong> data, make sure your
      | spreadsheet includes the minimal columns below. Requirements depend
      | on the <em>Billing Type</em> you’ll choose on the next screen.

    // ───────── Checklist ─────────
    ol.guide-steps
      li
        span.step-icon 1️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Billing Type (Info)
          |  – choose <em>Household</em> or <em>Account</em> on the next step.
      li
        span.step-icon 2️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Anchor ID (✅)
          |  – If Household: <em>Household ID</em> 
          |  - If Account: <em>Account Number</em>
      li
        span.step-icon 3️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Amount (✅)
          |  – the billed amount as a number (no currency symbols).
      li
        span.step-icon 4️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Period (Info)
          |  – You’ll select Month/Quarter/Year (and the specific month/quarter/year)
          | on the next step; your file does not need period columns.

    // ───────── Tips ─────────
    p.mt-3
      | • Keep <em>Household ID</em> or <em>Account Number</em> consistent to prevent duplicates.  
      br
      | • Keep <em>Amount</em> numeric (decimals allowed).  
      br
      | • You can start from our template to avoid formatting issues.

    // ───────── Download ─────────
    a.import-action-item.d-block.mt-2(
      href='/downloads/household-billing-import-template.xlsx'
      download
    )
      i.fas.fa-file-download.me-1
      | Download the household billing import template
    a.import-action-item.d-block.mt-2(
      href='/downloads/account-billing-import-template.xlsx'
      download
    )
      i.fas.fa-file-download.me-1
      | Download the account billing import template

    // ───────── Example header rows (both types) ─────────
    .example-header.mt-4
      h4 🧪 Example Header Row:
      p.mb-1
        code Household ID | Amount
      p
        code Account Number | Amount
